Package event.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AlreadyHasSpeakerException
    Throws when the organizer tries to add speaker to an event that has a speaker.
    DuplicateRoomNumberException
    Throws when the organizer tries to add a room with a room number that already exists.
    EventIsFullException
    Throws when user trying to add user to a full people event.
    InvalidNewMaxNumberException
    Throws when the new maximum number of people of an event is less than the existing attendees of that event.
    InvalidUserException
    Throws when the user does not exist.
    NoSpeakerException
    Throws when there is no such speaker.
    NoSuchConferenceException
    Throws when there is no such Conference.
    NoSuchEventException
    Throws when there is no such event.
    NoSuchTypeException
    Throws when there is no such type.
    NotInOfficeHourException
    Throws when the event is not between 9am to 5pm.
    RoomIsFullException
    Throws when user trying to add user to an event of a full room.
    TimeNotAvailableException
    Throws when the event contradicts with another event.
    TooManySpeakerException
    Throws when there are too many speakers more than maximum.
    WrongRoomSizeException
    Throws when the room size less than 1.
